edu.umass.cs.MHLClient.client

Class MobileIOClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.umass.cs.MHLClient.client.MobileIOClient

  • public class MobileIOClient
extends java.lang.Object
    The Mobile IO client is responsible for handling the server connection and sending data to the server. To connect to the server, instantiate a Mobile IO client instance and call connect(). If you register a ConnectionStateHandler using the setConnectionStateHandler(ConnectionStateHandler) method, then you can handle the ConnectionStateHandler.onConnected() and ConnectionStateHandler.onConnectionFailed(Exception) events.
